&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join frog?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since June 2021,&amp;nbsp;frog is part of Capgemini Invent.&amp;nbsp;We&amp;nbsp;partner with customer-centric enterprises to drive sustainable growth, by building and orchestrating experiences at scale, while harnessing the power of data and technology.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We’re&amp;nbsp;inventing the future of&amp;nbsp;brands and&amp;nbsp;customer experiences by delivering market-defining business models, products, services,&amp;nbsp;branding&amp;nbsp;and communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining frog means you’ll be joining the “pond,” a global network of studios, each with a thriving in-person and vibrant virtual culture. frogs are curious, collaborative, and courageous, united by our passion for improving the human experience through design, while each bringing our unique and diverse skills and experiences to the table. We draw on our global reach and local knowledge to solve complex problems and design innovative, sustainable solutions that touch hearts and move markets. frogs prize humour, positivity, and community just as highly as performance and outcomes. Our culture is open, flexible, inclusive, and engaging. Working at frog means being empowered to Make Your Mark on every project, in your studio, your community—and the world at large.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience Designers create digitally enabled products and services, applying skills across interaction design, visual design, and service design to develop holistic experiences from early concepts to detailed solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support teams on client-facing projects, pitches and internal initiatives.&amp;nbsp;You will learn by doing, with guidance from experienced practitioners who will help you understand&amp;nbsp;frog’s methodologies&amp;nbsp;and deliver&amp;nbsp;high-quality work&amp;nbsp;in the context of interdisciplinary projects.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project teams&amp;nbsp;rely on&amp;nbsp;Experience&amp;nbsp;Designers&amp;nbsp;to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create digital design artefacts including user flows, UI mock-ups, prototypes, journey maps, service blueprints, and ecosystem maps to communicate product&amp;nbsp;behaviour, experience concepts, and complex systems, including products in the GenAI space.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse&amp;nbsp;and benchmark existing solutions, identify pain points and opportunity spaces, and conduct foundational research and usability testing to generate actionable insights and inform design directions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-disciplinary teams to define project requirements by balancing user needs, market opportunities, business goals, and technical feasibility, while creating high-quality digital product experiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute detailed design concepts using strong interaction and visual design principles, applying holistic critical thinking and contributing across disciplines and workstreams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support successful project delivery through persuasive presentations, clear documentation, and effective handover of outcomes to clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business-level fluency in&amp;nbsp;both&amp;nbsp;English&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;German&amp;nbsp;is required.&amp;nbsp;Only in&amp;nbsp;exceptional cases of candidate with outstanding skills, are we considering non-German speaking applicants,&amp;nbsp;alongside a recently completed&amp;nbsp;a university degree in Interac

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join frog?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining frog means becoming part of &lt;strong&gt;“the pond”&lt;/strong&gt;—a global network of studios with thriving in-person and vibrant virtual cultures. frogs are curious, collaborative, and courageous—united by a passion for improving the human experience through design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At our Munich studio, you’ll be surrounded by a diverse team of strategists, designers, technologists, and researchers. We draw on global reach and deep local expertise to solve complex challenges and design innovative, sustainable solutions that move markets and touch hearts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe great design comes from a culture that values &lt;strong&gt;humour&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;community&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;craft&lt;/strong&gt; as much as outcomes. frog empowers every team member to &lt;strong&gt;Make Your Mark&lt;/strong&gt;—on projects, in your studio, and in the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you be doing?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Experience Designer&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;you will take full ownership of your workstream or lead a small team to deliver across digital products and experiences, from opportunity framing to detailed interaction and visual design and deliver with autonomy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll collaborate closely with cross-disciplinary teams to define and create experiences that meet functional and emotional needs, helping our clients to push boundaries in industries like healthcare, finance, mobility, and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will contribute to the business development including proposal writing and pitching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will contribute to a positive design team culture through collaboration, knowledge-sharing, and mentoring more junior practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In a project, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate strong project workstream leadership and client management capability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consolidate client objective, user needs, business requirements, and technical constraints to shape experience strategies and design solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, conduct or contribute to research, usability testing, and synthesis activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead benchmarking and analysis of existing product solutions and identify gaps or opportunity spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and articulate use cases, concepts and features across journeys, service blueprints, and interface behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive interaction logic and argumentation for the product or experience and create &lt;strong&gt;interaction model, information architecture, user flow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work confidently in &lt;strong&gt;Figma&lt;/strong&gt; and other design tools to digital design artefacts such as &lt;strong&gt;high-fidelity screens, interactive prototypes&lt;/strong&gt; to demonstrate product design and behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, apply and scale &lt;strong&gt;Design Systems&lt;/strong&gt; and including consulting on the strategic structure of the design system, creating and managing &lt;strong&gt;Figma&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;component library&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;style guide&lt;/strong&gt; and other &lt;strong&gt;documentation&lt;/strong&gt;, and driving &lt;strong&gt;governance&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;workflow&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;tool-chain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage your strong&lt;strong&gt; visual design craft&lt;/strong&gt;, including typography, layout, color theory and responsive design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the &lt;strong&gt;presentation&lt;/strong&gt; internally and externally with clarity, persuasion, and storytelling finesse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;W
